            <thetext>In general, it is the server&#39;s responsibility to ensure data integrity, but with more and more data processing done on the client-side there will be many use cases in which user-supplied json data needs to be checked. Also, when client and server are decoupled (as in the case of web services), there is a need to check data before it is processed - so that malformed data does break the client code.

There seems to be an emerging standard (http://json-schema.org/) with reference implementations. I actually don&#39;t know if this will be THE standard and how stable the specifications are at this point, but it might be worth to do more research on that.</thetext>
